Classes in edu.uchsc.ccp.dmap used by edu.uchsc.ccp.dmap
DMAPItem
          A DMAPItem is the basic unit of recognition in OpenDMAP.
DMAPLogger
          A facility for logging tracing messages in various ways.
DMAPPropertyFunctionException
          An exception to be thrown when an external object has a problem evaluating a property function.
DMAPPropertyFunctionHandler
          This interface allows external objects to handle DMAP slot property functions.
DMAPToken
          A DMAPToken is an input concept for the Parser.
DMAPTokenizer
          This class is the root of all DMAPTokenizer objects.
InfoPacket
          An InfoPacket is a binding between a DMAPItem that was expected in a pattern, and the specific value, or Reference that was matched against that item.
IReferenceHandler
          This is the interface that a Java class needs to implement in order to be a valid Reference handler withing OpenDMAP.
Parser
          The parser is the main entry point into the OpenDMAP system.
Pattern
          A pattern is what DMAP is looking to find in the input text.
Pattern.Operator
           
PatternGroup
          A PatternGroup is a collection of pattern fragments that are all waiting for the same next parser item to be recognized.
Prediction
          A Prediction is the heart of the DMAP parsing process.
PredictionEnvironment
          This class defines a binding environment for the pattern property constraints used by a prediction.
ProtegeProjectGroup
          This class represents a collection of Protege Knowledge Bases that are being used together in the OpenDMAP parser.
Reference
          A Reference is a description of something that DMAP has recognized in the input text.
